# Content Authoring

## Page structure

7 top-level sections, each a separate directory:

| Directory | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `culture/` | Identity — mission, vision, values, stance, practices, mood |
| `hiring/` | Joining & leaving the company |
| `onboarding/` | Post-hire ramp-up process |
| `work-style/` | How we work — remote, flex-time, leave, communication, projects, side-job |
| `systems/` | Policies — teian, coaching |
| `finance/` | Money — budget, salary, expenses, Meguri points, learning support |
| `tools/` | Internal tools & SaaS integrations |

- Every page belongs to one of these sections. Create a new section only if none fits.
- Never name a page the same as its parent directory. Use `index.mdx` (title: 概要) as the section-level summary page.
- When a concept spans systems and tools (e.g. teian, meguri), put Why/What in `systems/`, How in `tools/`, and cross-link.

## MDX frontmatter

Uses Fumadocs `pageSchema`. Minimum: `title`.

```mdx
---
title: Page Title
description: Optional description
---
```

## meta.json

Each directory has `meta.json` defining sidebar order. Values are filenames without extension.

```json
{ "title": "Section", "pages": ["index", "page-a", "page-b"] }
```

- `"---Label---"` inserts a separator
- Always add new pages to `meta.json`

## Built-in components

`<Cards>` + `<Card>`, `<Callout>`, `<Tabs>` + `<Tab>`

## Language

All content in Japanese.

- 本文は「ですます調」で統一する（である・だ・している → です・ます・しています）
- ただし箇条書きの体言止めはOK
